<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Simple hotel I stayed here with two of my friends during the Loveparade. It was a complete trip (bus plus hotel) so I don't know how much the hotel itself costs. The rooms were very simple, nothing to comment on it. Not large, but clean. Metrostation is just across the street, about 150 meters as far as I can remember.Breakfast was quite tasteless, even unpleasant, but maybe the hotel didn't bother since it was packed with Loveparade guests. Cheap dried out bread, tasteless cheese and salami, watery orange juice and german tea (tea tastes very sweet, like hot lemonade.) The hotel is quite far away from the centre of Berlin.So, it depends on what you're looking for: a cheap stay and nothing else (I recommend having your breakfast somewhere else), then you should be fine in this hotel. 
